article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 74, Louisiana Tech 65
article.story: LITTLE ROCK, Ark. -- Solomon Bozeman scored 23 points and Alex Garcia-Mendoza added 17 as Arkansas-Little Rock rode a hot-shooting second half to a 74-65 victory against Louisiana Tech on Friday. Daylon Guy had 12 points for the Trojans (4-2), who shot 14.8 percent (4 of 27) from the floor in the first half but 69.6 percent (16 of 23) after intermission. DeAndre Brown scored 24 points and Olu Ashaolu 11 for the Bulldogs (5-2), whose five-game winning streak ended. After a pair of Brown free throws made the score 56-54 in Arkansas-Little Rock's favor, the Trojans took control. Two baskets by Bozeman, one of them a 3-pointer, highlighted a run that resulted in a 70-61 cushion with 1:13 to play. Derrick Bails scored 11 points for Arkansas-Little Rock. Guy had eight rebounds.
